<p>
<seg id=1> According to the human rights organization-Tibet Information Network-whose headquarters are in London, Agya Rinpoche, one of the most popular religious leaders in Tibet, fled to America to show his protest against the Chinese policy on Tibet. </seg>
<seg id=2> According to Tibet Information Network, Agya Rinpoche expressed his indignation that Beijing tried to reform the mosques in Tibet that was in harassment, and refused to accept the Pretender Panchen Lama, who was made by the Dalai Lama. </seg>
<seg id=3> However, Tibet Information Network was not sure whether Agya Rinpoche planned to shelter in America. </seg>
</p>
